<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-03-25T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-03-25T13:00:00-05:00" n="223" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d223">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">123R914/125: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The High Commissioner in Haiti</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Russell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Port-au-Prince</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-03-25T13:00:00-05:00">March 25, 1929—1
                                p.m.</date><lb/>[Received 8:33 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>24. Unless otherwise instructed I propose to withhold action on the
                            Department’s instruction number 406, March 14, 1929, sending a request
                            for reconsideration of certain features therein contained. My despatch
                            discussing these features will be forwarded by next pouch.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Russell</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>